All your forms should be defined as subclasses of FlaskForm
--> They are

and should have properly defined validators.
--> Validtors are either part of the form or in the function creating the data send to csv, but are checked anyway

Your forms should be handled properly, by defining a route accepting GET and POST methods,
--> They do

and you should use the POST/REDIRECT/GET pattern when the form data validates (as shown in class).


Your web site data should be stored in files, located in the data subfolder. 
The data should in CSV or JSON formats.
--> accounts.csv
--> blog_posts.csv
--> github_projects.csv
--> messages.csv

