Submission:

Zip your project folder and submit it on Moodle before the due date and time. Make sure your zip file does NOT contain any Python virtual environment. Points will be deducted if your submission includes Python virtual environments. Name your file following this regular expression: /^SOEN287_A3_\d{8}_[A-Za-z]+\.zip$/. The file name should include your student ID and your name.

Grading
Total: 15 Points
Grading Scheme
Grading Criteria	Description	Points
Demo	You will have to demo your web site to a TA. You will have to give an overview of your web site, go through the different pages, 
demo the features:
    -log in, 
    -submit forms, 
    -additional features, etc...)

    You will also have to answer at least one question from the TA. Your answer(s) will be graded. Your demo, not counting the time for questions and answers, should take no more than 5 minutes.	
    8 points
Source Code	Code quality (running code, no bugs, documented code, code organization, ...). Good use of template inheritance and other Flask packages (WTForms, csv, ...). Project folder organization (subfolders, file naming, ...). All features implemented properly.	7 points